Here are some software you can use for building a schematic of a arduino system online:

#Circuito.io: https://www.circuito.io/
This is a web-based prototyping tool that allows you to design electronic circuits and generate a detailed Bill of Materials, wiring guide, and test code for your circuit. It supports both Arduino and Raspberry Pi projects 1.

#Fritzing: https://wiredraw.co/schematic-diagram-online-arduino/
This is another popular option that provides a comprehensive set of tools for creating and editing diagrams. It also supports Arduino projects 2.

#Autodesk Circuits: https://www.makeuseof.com/free-schematic-drawing-software-arduino-raspberry-pi/
This is a cloud-based platform that allows you to design, simulate, and share electronic circuits. It supports both Arduino and Raspberry Pi projects 3.
